    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Technique used in computer imaging to counteract the jagged effect seen in curved or diagonal lines, caused by pixelation. It involves the interpolation of intermediate colors where differing colors meet on computer monitors and printouts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009221/Cotton and Oliver, Cyberspace Lexicon (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047672/McGraw-Hill Encyclopedia of Science and Technology Online (2000-2004)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beeldvormende techniek voor computers die het rafelige effect bij kromme of diagonale lijnen als gevolg van de pixelopbouw tegengaat. Het principe berust op het invoegen van tussenkleuren op plaatsen waar verschillende kleuren naast elkaar verschijnen op computermonitors en uitdraaien.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052667/Biemond, Woordenboek Automatisering (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>電腦成像的技術，用以消除在弧線或斜線中，由像素導致的凹凸鋸齒。在電腦螢幕與印出的資料中，利用中介顏色在不同顏色交會處進行插補。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
